					<h1>Prototyping Assumptions</h1>
					<p>Using the storyboards we developed, we started prototyping to test our assumptions around the interactions and electronic forms of our dolls. We used paper cups to talk with education researchers and primary school teachers to iterate on different interactions. Once we determined how the dolls would be played with, we began prototyping with electronic components to see if we can determine distinct emotions. </p>
				</div>

